Just a general tip, I would not select on tag names.  Doing so may end up interfering with new HTML added in the future, like say, a list of navigation items.  Give each list item a specific class name, like `todoListItem` and select on that instead with `querySelectorAll(&#39;.todoListItem&#39;)`.  I also think this will be easier if you start with an empty list and populate it based on data.  In other words run everything through your addNewItem function.  Then, if you add an event listener to the delete button within this scope, it should apply to only the current item.

```js
const addNewItem = text =&gt; {

    //... trimmed

    li.textContent = text

    deleteBtn.addEventListener(&#39;click&#39;,
      () =&gt; li.remove())

   // ... trimmed
}
```

